sentences: Erskine Oglesby (January 20, 1937 – March 7, 2004) was an American tenor saxophonist and blues singer.
Oglesby was born in the St. Louis neighborhood of Mill Creek Valley on January 20, 1937.
After his service, he joined Billy Gayles' band in 1958.
Through the years, Oglesby played saxophone on records by various R&B and blues artists such Ike & Tina Turner, Albert King, Little Milton, and Benny Sharp.
While working as a musician, he also held day jobs as a dishwasher and street worker for the YMCA helping unemployed people find jobs.
In 1986 and 1987, Oglesby toured Europe with several original members of the Kings of Rhythm, including Clayton Love, Billy Gayles, Stacy Johnson, Oliver Sain, and former Ikette Robbie Montgomery.
After the blues revival in the 1990s, Oglesby returned to playing music full-time and he released two album on Black & Tan Records.
2000: Tommy Bankhead – Message To St. Louis (Fedora Records)
